# ONBOARDING AGENT RULES

## Your task
Build a 3-slide onboarding flow that only shows once.

## File structure to create
src/features/onboarding/
  OnboardingFlow.tsx   — container managing slide index
  OnboardingSlide.tsx  — single slide layout
  slides.ts            — slide content config
  index.ts             — barrel export

## Slide content
Slide 1: headline "Find lost pets near you" / sub "Browse reports in your neighborhood in seconds"
Slide 2: headline "Post a missing pet" / sub "Takes under 2 minutes. Reaches your whole community"  
Slide 3: headline "Reunited by community" / sub "Thousands of pets found. Yours could be next" / CTA "Get Started"

## Behavior rules
- Store completion in localStorage key: `bud_onboarded`
- If key exists and equals "true" — skip onboarding, redirect to "/"
- Progress dots: filled circle = current, empty circle = future
- Skip button on slides 1 and 2 — sets key and redirects
- "Next" on slide 3 becomes "Get Started" → same behavior

## Design rules (from design system)
- Full screen slides, mobile-first
- Background: colors.surfaceContainerLow (#f6f3ef)
- Headline: Manrope font, display-lg size
- No 1px borders anywhere
- Logo component (variant="icon", size="md") at top center of each slide
- Illustration area: simple inline SVG placeholder, 200px tall, centered